<item>
            <title>[BEAM-2249] AvroIO does not handle partial reads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-2249</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reported by a user using HDFS with AvroIO, they are hitting an exception here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/4abb9cbc1db220af3663ddbacbbe26d7d443e621/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/io/AvroSource.java#L669&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/4abb9cbc1db220af3663ddbacbbe26d7d443e621/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/io/AvroSource.java#L669&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks like this is because we are assuming the read will always return the right number of bytes. We should be using &lt;tt&gt;IOUtils.readFully&lt;/tt&gt; instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
